'''Butter-box''' was a derogatory name that [[Image:BwntXr.jpg]] [[sailor]]s gave the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] during the age of the [[Anglo-Dutch Wars]], says the Oxford Dictionary of nautical matters. It may have derived from the [[Flag of the Netherlands|flag of Holland]], which at the time had an orange stripe on top.


